# StomaTrack Account and Data Deletion Instructions

Last Updated: April 17, 2026

StomaTrack allows users to delete their account and associated data at any time. These instructions explain how to permanently delete your account from within the app.

By completing the steps below, your account and associated data stored by StomaTrack will be deleted.

## How to Delete Your Account

1. Open the StomaTrack app.
2. Go to the Settings page.
3. Scroll to the bottom of the page.
4. Tap the Delete Account button.
5. Follow any on-screen prompts to confirm the deletion request.

## What Happens When You Delete Your Account

When you use the Delete Account button, your account and associated data will be permanently deleted from StomaTrack, subject to any limited retention that may be required by law or for legitimate operational purposes.

Associated data may include:

- Ostomy output data
- Fluid or water intake records
- Medication records
- Notes, logs, symptoms, or other health-related entries entered into the app
- Account information, if applicable

Once the deletion process is completed, your account cannot be restored.

## Important Information

Please make sure you want to permanently delete your account before using this feature. After deletion, you may lose access to information previously stored in the app.

If you experience any issues using the Delete Account button, you may contact us for assistance.

